UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Nora RODRIGUEZ-GONZALEZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 15-41691

Conference Calendar

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Filed: 06/21/2016 Renata Ann Gowie, Assistant U.S. Attorney, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appel-lee. Marjorie A. Meyers, Federal Public Defender, Philip G. Gallagher, Assistant Federal Public Defender, Houston, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Before JONES, CLEMENT, and OWEN, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

Appealing the judgment in a criminal case, Nora Rodriguez-Gonzalez raises an argument that is foreclosed by United States v. Betancourt, 586 F.3d 303, 308-09 (5th Cir. 2009), which held that knowledge of drug type and quantity is not an element of a 21 U.S.C. § 841 offense. Accordingly, the motion for summary disposition is GRANTED, and the judgment of the district court is AFFIRMED.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
